&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;trebuchet ms&#39;, geneva, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How We Work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;trebuchet ms&#39;, geneva, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our culture is inclusive, collaborative, fast-paced, and data-driven. We’ve been certified as a Great Place to Work® for four consecutive years, based on feedback from our own team.&amp;nbsp;If you want to make an impact while propelling your career forward, we’d love to hear from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.3; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;trebuchet ms&#39;, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Are Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.3; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The Sr. Manager of Creative Ops is responsible for creating structure and scalable processes to creative production to optimize timelines, capacity and costs. The right candidate will posses a strong understanding and passion for systems and tools behind the product life cycle and a desire to manage change by building capabilities through people, process and tools. A strong desire to master Ai and infiltrate through organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.3; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &#39;trebuchet ms&#39;, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Own And How You Will Make A Difference&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the seamless flow of our in-house creative organization ensuring effective decision-making, cross-functional collaboration, and a positive team experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate the management of all major creative projects, determining critical timelines and key milestones in the creative development process, including budget, talent, and schedule etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain key relationships with internal &amp;amp; external partners and stakeholders, driving a culture of collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the liaison between production, marketing, merchandising, product and creative.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain annual GTM and seasonal shoot calendars, overseeing and aligning production and post-production timelines with merchandising and marketing schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the management of financial operations by forecasting creative operations budget; negotiating statements of work, ensuring work is delivered on budget, and invoicing clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage improvements and efficiencies to creative marketing tools, documentation and processes, including exploration and implementation of AI opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the VP/Creative Director to continuously evolve our organization in line with our strategy,

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Objective&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work collaboratively to strengthen ThirdLove’s social media community engagement and growth, and increase brand identity, awareness, and visual presence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be on the front lines of building and strengthening ThirdLove’s organic social community as you’ll create content and&lt;br&gt;write copy for daily consumer-facing content. Through connecting with the ThirdLove audience via creative output, bringing&lt;br&gt;fresh eyes and ideas to the team, flexing your creative problem-solving skills, and maintaining a positive and energetic spirit,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;you will be a valued and respected new member of the organic social team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Content Creation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;○ Capture lofi video and static content at all Los Angeles held photoshoots and events&lt;br&gt;○ Create engaging social-first content for ThirdLove and Kit Undergarments – from Reels, TikToks, IG Stories,&lt;br&gt;memes, and more!&lt;br&gt;○ Write on-brand copy to support visual assets (from IG Stories, captions, video text overlay, etc.)&lt;br&gt;○ Visually plan the IG grid in collaboration with the team&lt;br&gt;○ Collaborate with the team on innovative creative concepts to support strategy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Social Listening&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;○ Stay up-to-date with trending topics and communicate relevant opportunities to the team&lt;br&gt;○ Identify trending audios on a weekly basis to support Reels and TikToks&lt;br&gt;○ Stay up-to-date on tagged UGC and identify opportunities to repurpose content on ThirdLove’s&lt;br&gt;owned channels&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Admin&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;○ Post assets as planned (Reels, TikToks, IG Stories, etc)&lt;br&gt;○ With close attention to detail, efficiently schedule content utilizing Dash Hudson&lt;br&gt;○ Aid in the reporting process by keeping Dash Hudson boards and campaigns up to date on a&lt;br&gt;weekly basis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Various other tasks and duties as assigned or needed&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Physical Demands (Walking, lifting, equipment, operation, etc.)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;This position is mostly remote, but occasionally the employee must physically be in the office. The following physical demands and&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;their onsite equivalents should be taken into consideration.&lt;/em&gt;● Stand or Sit: Must be able to remain in a stationary position approximately 60% of the time&lt;br&gt;● Use hands/fingers to handle or feel: Constantly operate a computer and other office productivity machinery, such as a&lt;br&gt;calculator, copy machine, computer, printer, etc.&lt;br&gt;● See: The ability to observe details at close range like digital writing (within a few feet of the observer).&lt;br&gt;● Talk &amp;amp; Speak clearly: The ability to verbally communicate information and ideas so others will understand. Must be able to&lt;br&gt;exchange accurate information in these situations, many of these interactions can be online and require verbal exchanges.&lt;br&gt;● Hear &amp;amp; Verbal Comprehension: The ability to listen to what other colleagues verbally express and understand the&lt;br&gt;information that has been provided.&lt;br&gt;● Walk: The person in this position needs to occasionally move about inside the office to access file cabinets, office&lt;br&gt;machinery, etc.&lt;br&gt;● Thought Processing: be able to make logical connections between thoughts and/or actions. Be able to understand their&lt;br&gt;relevance to achieve a goal or keep the thread of conversation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education, Work Experience &amp;amp; Special Skills/Licenses&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Bachelor&#39;s degree preferred, but not required&lt;br&gt;● Knowledge of Ado

